If you want it to run at 00:00 every 21st day of the month:  
`0 0 21 * *` (at 00:00 on day-of-month 21).

If you want it to run at 12:00 every 21st day of the month:  
`0 12 21 * *` (at 12:00 on day-of-month 21).

If you want it to run every 21 days, no matter the day of month, then I&#39;m afraid that&#39;s not possible using node-cron and also most other similar scheduling systems.

In that specific case you&#39;d have to track the days yourself and calculate the next day it should run at by adding 21 days to the current date whenever the function runs.

If you want to play around with cron schedules, I recommend [crontab.guru][1].

If you want to add the 21 days yourself, you can use setInterval to schedule a function to run at a specific time:

```js
const waitSeconds = 1814400; // 21 days

function scheduledFunction() {
  // Do something
}

// Run now
scheduledFunction();

// Run every 21 days
setInterval(scheduledFunction, waitSeconds);
```

However, keep in mind that the internal clock might be inaccurate so there can be quite a few seconds of difference.


  [1]: https://crontab.guru/#0_12_21_*_*

