Let&#39;s say you have a `QuerySnapshot snapshot` at the ready. You can calculate the sum of all values like so:

    final sum = snapshot.data.documents.fold(0, (prev, next) =&gt; prev + int.parse(next[&#39;Value&#39;]))

In other words, folding should be performed on `List&lt;DocumentSnapshot&gt;`.

**Edit in response to updated code:**

The culprit are these lines:

    var one = int.parse(getValueSTRING);
    var list2 = [one];
    var sum2 = list2.fold(0, (curr, next) =&gt; curr + next);

The problem is that the code tries to fold a list that has only one value. Summing list with one item will always net a sum equal to that item&#39;s value. 

To get the correct value all `DocumentSnapshots` need to be taken into account. Currently, only one `DocumentSnapshot` is considered, as indicated by this line:

    DocumentSnapshot documentSnapshot = snapshot.data.documents[index];

Instead, try something like this (I&#39;ve omitted unnecessary code to reduce visual noise):

    &lt;...&gt;
    builder: (context, snapshot) {
      // Add this line to calculate total sum, and use it later on
      final sum = snapshot.data.documents.fold(0.0, (prev, next) =&gt; prev + int.parse(next[&#39;Value&#39;]))
      return ListView.builder(&lt;...&gt;);


